footnotes = }} Euless is a city in Tarrant County, Texas, United States. It is a suburb of Dallas and Fort Worth. As of the 2020 census, 61,032 people lived there. The southwestern part of Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport is inside the city limits of Euless. == References == Category:Cities in Texas Category:Settlements in Tarrant County, Texas
